    "In the evaluation of MediGuide-14B's performance across different insurance types, the group demonstrated notable results in the realm of Supplementary Diagnosis accuracy.",
    "For cases covered under the URRBMI, the MediGuide-14B achieved a mean accuracy of 83.65%, under the UEBMI category, the mean accuracy recorded was slightly higher, at 85.04% (P=0.046).",
    "(Supplementary Figure S6)",
    "Medical history is crucial in diagnosis, offering insights into a patient's past health and disease risk factors.",
    "While human doctors can interpret this data based on experience, LLMs face a challenge in doing so effectively."
